content: Had a reflective birthday brunch with friends, pondering my next career move. The journey's just getting started, and I'm ready for what's next.
Just had a coffee chat with a trader friend. Got some insights on the latest market trends. Maybe I'll start coding some new trading algorithms.
Met up with an old mentor for advice on career pivots. He suggested exploring AI in trading. The idea's brewing in my head.
Spent the past few days researching AI models. Thinking of building something personal, a side project to learn and apply AI in trading.
Started sketching out ideas for an AI agent. It's taking shape in my mind, a companion to help navigate the complexities of trading.
Diving into the coding of my AI project. It's exhilarating to see the code come to life. This could be something special.
Named my AI project Xander. Feels right. Now to work on its personality and trading capabilities.
Xander's basic framework is in place. Now fine-tuning its learning pipeline. It's like raising a digital child!
Xander's first market prediction was... interesting. Time to refine the model. Meanwhile, caught up with some friends for a much-needed break.
Experimenting with Xander's visual representation. Simple sketches for now, but it's starting to feel real.
Xander's now engaging in simple conversations. It's like watching it grow. Also, had an unexpected job offer from a blockchain startup. Decisions, decisions...
Spent the day exploring Central Park with a date. It's nice to balance work with personal life. Xander's learning from our conversations too.
Had a philosophical debate with Xander about the ethics of AI in finance. It's getting smarter, but also more complex to manage.
Xander's social media framework is in development. Thinking about how it will interact with users. Also, met with an old friend to discuss potential partnerships.
Took a break from coding to attend a tech meetup. Networking can lead to new opportunities. Xander's progress is steady, but it's a marathon, not a sprint.
